Ondo State Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, on Wednesday sacked all political appointees. Those affected were Personal Assistants, Special Assistants and Senior Special Assistants. A statement by the Chief Press Secretary to Governor Akeredolu, Richard Olabode Olatinde, said the Governor immediately announced appointment of 40 aides including SAs and SSAs. The statement said the Governor approved appointment of Bola Alabi as the new Chief of Protocol while Mrs. Olufunke Bisi Aruna was appointed as the Deputy Chief of Protocol. It said Mr. Kunle Adebayo and two other committee members were asked to continue to superintend over the affairs of the OSRC Media Group as Chairman and members. The Nation By Ayodeji Alabi Akure - Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State, on Sunday, approved the appointment of Messrs Dapo Adepoju, Adebiyi Mayowa and Olufunmi Felix as his Special Assistants on Youth Mobilisation. This was contained in a statement issued in Akure by the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Mr… In "News" By Ayodeji Alabi Akure - Gov. Oluwarotimi Akeredolu of Ondo State on Monday approved the appointment of Mr Tolu Fadahunsi , as the Director-General of the Ondo State Bureau for Public Procurement. Mr Segun Ajiboye, Chief Press Secretary to the governor, in a press statement in Akure, said the appointment… In "News" ADO-EKITI - Gov. Ayo Fayose of  Ekiti State has approved the appointment of Dr Modupe Alade as the Secretary to the State Government. Also approved was the appointment of Mr Idowu Adelusi as the Chief Press Secretary to the Governor. The appointments, which were made public in a statement in Akure… In "News"